<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-03-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-03-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="62" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d62">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 3691/243.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Brown</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.—Extract.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-03-27"><hi rend="italic">March 27,
                                1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Informs Mr. Root that Tegucigalpa was abandoned early yesterday
                            precipitately and occupied last night by the Nicaraguan and
                            revolutionary forces. Also informs Mr. Root that he assumed charge in
                            the interval with aid of consuls to preserve order.</p>
                    </div>
